      • addMedia

        public void addMedia(Map<String,Object> params,
            ISirqulCallback<AssetResponse> callback)
        Uploads an asset to s3 server and returns an asset id which can be used to assign to various objects.

        Target API Endpoint: /asset/create

        Available parameters for this api
        • SirqulKeys.accountId of type Long
          the account ID of the user (deviceId or accountId required)
        • SirqulKeys.assetId
          the asset id (optional) if you want to replace the asset but keep the same id, same permissions, same notes etc
        • SirqulKeys.albumId
          the album the asset will be added to (optional)
        • SirqulKeys.collectionId
          the collection id
        • SirqulKeys.addToDefaultAlbum
          the add to default album
        • SirqulKeys.caption
          the caption (optional)
        • SirqulKeys.locationDescription
          the location description (optional)
        • SirqulKeys.location of type Location
          the location (optional)
        • SirqulKeys.notificationMessage
          the notification message
        • SirqulKeys.mediaFilePath
          the media file path
        • SirqulKeys.attachedMediaFilePath
          the attached media file path containing an asset that the "media" file references (optional). Example to upload a video: the "media" file should contain a screen capture of the video, and the "attachedMedia" should be the actual video.
        • SirqulKeys.attachedMediaUrl
          this can be used if the "attachedMedia" is a link (i.e. a Youtube video, etc) (optional)

        SirqulResponse subclass type:
        a AssetResponse on valid response, or SirqulResponse with error message
        Parameters:
        params - the Map<String, Object> containing the parameters, both required and any optional ones you wish to send through to this api.
        callback - an optional ISirqulCallback instance that handles your response from this Sirqul API call. With this, API responses are automatically checked for validity or invalidity, whether it was null entirely, and to throw a SirqulException for any and all Exception's that may have occurred. Each of these cases are broken up into separate interface methods. If you foresee yourself needing to handle all cases, it's recommended you simply instantiate a new ISirqulCallback instance, which will force you to implement all methods. If you really only care about one or a few of them, you can use the SirqulCallback class, which you can optionally override any of those same interface methods. If you wish to ignore any response, simply pass in null for this.
        See Also:
        AssetApiBase.addMedia

      • updateMedia

        public void updateMedia(Map<String,Object> params,
               ISirqulCallback<SirqulResponse> callback)
        Updates an asset's meta data. If an album reference is passed in, the participants with write permissions are allowed to edit the asset. Otherwise, only the asset up-loader has permission to edit the data.

        Target API Endpoint: /asset/update

        Available parameters for this api
        • SirqulKeys.accountId of type Long
          the account ID of the user (deviceId or accountId required, deviceId is sent automatically)
        • SirqulKeys.assetId
          the ID of the asset to update
        • SirqulKeys.albumId
          the ID of the album to check user permissions
        • SirqulKeys.attachedAssetId
          the ID of the attached asset
        • SirqulKeys.caption
          the caption
        • SirqulKeys.locationDescription
          the location description
        • SirqulKeys.location of type Location
          the location used to update the asset's location

        SirqulResponse subclass type:
        a SirqulResponse with a message of success or fail
        Parameters:
        params - the Map<String, Object> containing the parameters, both required and any optional ones you wish to send through to this api.
        callback - an optional ISirqulCallback instance that handles your response from this Sirqul API call. With this, API responses are automatically checked for validity or invalidity, whether it was null entirely, and to throw a SirqulException for any and all Exception's that may have occurred. Each of these cases are broken up into separate interface methods. If you foresee yourself needing to handle all cases, it's recommended you simply instantiate a new ISirqulCallback instance, which will force you to implement all methods. If you really only care about one or a few of them, you can use the SirqulCallback class, which you can optionally override any of those same interface methods. If you wish to ignore any response, simply pass in null for this.
